      • getDomainNameLabel

        public String getDomainNameLabel()
        Optional. Gets or sets the Domain name label.The concatenation of the domain name label and the regionalized DNS zone make up the fully qualified domain name associated with the public IP address. If a domain name label is specified, an A DNS record is created for the public IP in the Microsoft Azure DNS system.
        Returns:
        The DomainNameLabel value.

If a domain name label is specified, an A DNS record is created for the public IP in the Microsoft Azure DNS system.

      • getFqdn

        public String getFqdn()
        Optional. Gets the FQDN, Fully qualified domain name of the A DNS record associated with the public IP. This is the concatenation of the domainNameLabel and the regionalized DNS zone.
        Returns:
        The Fqdn value.

      • getReverseFqdn

        public String getReverseFqdn()
        Optional. Gets or Sests the Reverse FQDN. A user-visible, fully qualified domain name that resolves to this public IP address. If the reverseFqdn is specified, then a PTR DNS record is created pointing from the IP address in the in-addr.arpa domain to the reverse FQDN.
        Returns:
        The ReverseFqdn value.

      • setReverseFqdn

        public void setReverseFqdn(String reverseFqdnValue)
        Optional. Gets or Sests the Reverse FQDN. A user-visible, fully qualified domain name that resolves to this public IP address. If the reverseFqdn is specified, then a PTR DNS record is created pointing from the IP address in the in-addr.arpa domain to the reverse FQDN.
        Parameters:
        reverseFqdnValue - The ReverseFqdn value.
